      "text": [
        ": «لاَ تَقْضِ وَتْرَ لَيْلَتِكَ يَعْنِي فِي اَلْعِيدَيْنِ إِنْ كَانَ فَاتَكَ حَتَّى تُصَلِّيَ اَلزَّوَالَ فِي ذَلِكَ اَلْيَوْمِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1470 - Hariz narrated from Zurarah from Abu Abdullah Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\n\"Do not make up the Witr prayer of your night, meaning on the two Eids, if you missed it until you have prayed the midday (Dhuhr) prayer on that day.\""
        ]
      }
